## Step 2: Calculate the probability of drawing two balls of the same color
The probability of drawing a red ball from the first urn is $\frac{8}{15}$, and the probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn is $\frac{r}{r+9}$. Thus, the probability of drawing two red balls is $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r+9}$. The probability of drawing a blue ball from the first urn is $\frac{7}{15}$, and from the second urn is $\frac{9}{r+9}$. So, the probability of drawing two blue balls is $\frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r+9}$. The total probability of drawing two balls of the same color is $\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r+9} + \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r+9}$.

