Since $E_{1, \text{Ps}} = \frac{1}{2} E_1$ due to $\mu = \frac{m_e}{2}$, and knowing $E_1 = -13.6 \, \mathrm{eV}$, we have $E_{1, \text{Ps}} = \frac{1}{2} \times (-13.6 \, \mathrm{eV}) = -6.8 \, \mathrm{eV}$.

