For a sample of size $n = 12$, the mean $\bar{X}$ has a mean of $\mu_{\bar{X}} = \mu = 0.5$ and a variance of $\sigma_{\bar{X}}^2 = \frac{\sigma^2}{n} = \frac{1/12}{12} = \frac{1}{144}$.

## Step 4
