To approximate $P(1/2 \leq \bar{X} \leq 2/3)$, we need to standardize the values 1/2 and 2/3 to z-scores using the formula $z = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu}{\sigma_{\bar{X}}}$. For $\bar{X} = 1/2 = 0.5$, $z = \frac{0.5 - 0.5}{0.0833} = 0$. For $\bar{X} = 2/3 \approx 0.6667$, $z = \frac{0.6667 - 0.5}{0.0833} \approx 2$.

