Using a standard normal distribution, we look up the probabilities corresponding to the z-scores. $P(0 \leq Z \leq 2)$, where $Z$ is a standard normal variable, gives us the desired probability since the distribution is symmetric around 0 and $P(Z \leq 0) = 0.5$. $P(Z \leq 2) \approx 0.9772$, so $P(0 \leq Z \leq 2) = 0.9772 - 0.5 = 0.4772$.

