We are asked to find the probability that the length of life of the bulb from company $A$ exceeds the length of life of the bulb from company $B$ by at least 15 hours. This can be expressed as $P(X - Y \geq 15)$, where $X$ represents the length of life of the bulb from company $A$ and $Y$ represents the length of life of the bulb from company $B$.

